descript.abstract: Last updated in 2001 via the Seattle Landslide Study. The original data was created from City of Seattle State Environmental Policy Act (SEPA) maps which table digitized in 1995 using earlier mapping performed by Donald Tubbs. This layer was modified by Shannon and Wilson to include runoff zones and edge smoothing.
descript.purpose: To implement and regulate the City of Seattle's Environmentally Critical Areas policies.
